{
  "text": "Based on both field and laboratory studies, conditiondependent mate choice or preference occurs in this population of bushy-tailed woodrats. More specifically, males with lower MCV had greater reproductive success and were also preferred by females over males of higher MCV. While many studies have linked condition-dependent traits to female preference in the laboratory or reproductive success in the field [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] , no study, to our knowledge, has used the same males to assess mating patterns and preference both in the laboratory and in the field.",
  "citation_candidates": [
